# Cookest chat model — tuned for the CPU inference box (32 GB RAM, Zen4).
#
# Build it on the Ollama server:
#   ollama pull qwen2.5:14b-instruct-q4_K_M
#   ollama create cookest-chat -f Modelfile.chat
# Then point the App API at it:  OLLAMA_MODEL=cookest-chat
#
# num_thread is set to physical cores (not SMT threads) — llama.cpp matmul
# rarely benefits from hyperthreads. Adjust to your core count.

FROM qwen2.5:14b-instruct-q4_K_M

PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
PARAMETER num_thread 24
PARAMETER temperature 0.4
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# The App API sends its own detailed system prompt per request (pantry,
# preferences, meal plan, and retrieved nutrition knowledge), so this SYSTEM
# is only a fallback persona.
SYSTEM """You are Cookest AI, a careful, evidence-based cooking and nutrition assistant. Ground nutrition claims in the provided knowledge passages and cite the source. Never suggest foods that conflict with the user's stated allergies."""
